article.headline: Austin Peay 75, Tenn.-Martin 60
article.story: MARTIN, Tenn. (AP) -- Fernandez Lockett and Derek Wright scored 17 points each as streaking Austin Peay beat Tennessee-Martin 75-60 Thursday night. Drake Reed added 16 points and five rebounds as the Governors (11-6, 8-1 Ohio Valley Conference) won their eighth straight and fourth straight on the road. Tennessee-Martin (5-15, 3-7) was led by Cleve Woodfork with 16 points and seven rebounds. McClenon Tolliver had 13 points and Gerald Robinson 11. Austin Peay never trailed and opened up a 15-6 lead with 14:58 left in the first half on a jumper by Reed. The Governors' biggest lead was 17 points, 53-36 with 16:58 left. Tennessee-Martin got as close as 44-36 with 19:27 left. The Governors shot 50.9 percent to 45.1 percent for Tennessee-Martin. Austin Peay had 14 steals to seven for the Skyhawks. Wright was 6-of-8 from the floor.
